Differential diagnosis . The new species is most similar to
P. foliiger (
Mahunka and Mahunka-Papp, 1980
)
by the short and smooth pseudanal setae and similar relative lengths of the hysterosomal setae. It differs from
P. foliiger
by the simple pseudanal setae (vs. foliate in
P. foliiger
) and not swollen base of solenidion ω 1 of tibiotarsus I (vs. base of solenidion ω 1 of tibiotarsus I distinctly swollen in
P. foliiger
). Additionally setae f are distinctly longer than h 1 (vs. f and h 1 subequal in
P. foliiger
).
